<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="83" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Soreng, Cabi &amp; L. J. Gillespie" baseAuthorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa diaphora var. songarica" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="diaphora" variety="songarica">Poa diaphora var. songarica</taxonomicName>
was recently recorded (as 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa songarica" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="songarica">Eremopoa songarica</taxonomicName>
; determination verified here) from one locality in northernmost Israel (Danin and Fragman-Sapir 2016+). It was collected as a waif in Canada (Manitoba) in the 1950s (
<bibRefCitation author="Stevenson, GA" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Field Naturalist" pageId="23" pageNumber="92" pagination="174 - 177" refId="B59" refString="Stevenson, GA, 1965. Notes on the more recently adventive flora of the Brandon area, Manitoba. Canadian Field Naturalist 79: 174 - 177" title="Notes on the more recently adventive flora of the Brandon area, Manitoba." volume="79" year="1965">Stevenson 1965</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. persica" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="persica">E. persica</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Darbyshire, SJ" journalOrPublisher="143. Univ. of Karachi, Karachi" pageId="21" pageNumber="90" refId="B18" refString="Darbyshire, SJ, 2007. Eremopoa Roshev. In: Flora of North America Editorial Committee (Eds) Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol. 24. Oxford University Press, New York, 618-619." title="Eremopoa Roshev. In: Flora of North America Editorial Committee (Eds) Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol. 24. Oxford University Press, New York, 618 - 619." year="2007">Darbyshire 2007</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. altaica" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="altaica">E. altaica</taxonomicName>
: re-identified here), but is apparently not persistent (
<bibRefCitation author="Darbyshire, SJ" journalOrPublisher="143. Univ. of Karachi, Karachi" pageId="21" pageNumber="90" refId="B18" refString="Darbyshire, SJ, 2007. Eremopoa Roshev. In: Flora of North America Editorial Committee (Eds) Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol. 24. Oxford University Press, New York, 618-619." title="Eremopoa Roshev. In: Flora of North America Editorial Committee (Eds) Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol. 24. Oxford University Press, New York, 618 - 619." year="2007">Darbyshire 2007</bibRefCitation>
, B.A. Ford, pers. comm, 2018).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="83">
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvelev, NN" journalOrPublisher="Botaniceski Zurnal (Moscow &amp; Leningrad)" pageId="23" pageNumber="92" refId="B67" refString="Tzvelev, NN, 1976. Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1-788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" title="Zlaki SSSR. Nauka Publishers, Leningrad Section, Leningrad, 1 - 788 [English translation: 1983. Grasses of the Soviet Union, 2 vols. Amerind Publishing Co. New Delhi.]" year="1976">Tzvelev (1976</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 480) cited &quot;In herbidis Songaria ad rivulum Tschulak [Jun 1841], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">Karelin &amp; Kiriloff 2123</emphasis>
&quot; (LE!) as type of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. subtilis" pageId="14" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="subtilis">P. subtilis</taxonomicName>
(duplicates at BM000959360 image!, K000789846 image!, BR0000006600860 image!, P02663388!, P02663405!), but the type is the one [1840] collection cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Karelin, GS" journalOrPublisher="PLoS One" pageId="21" pageNumber="90" refId="B32" refString="Karelin, GS, Kiriloff, IP, 1841. Enumeratio plantarum in desertis Songariae orientalis. Moscow, 233 pp." title="Enumeratio plantarum in desertis Songariae orientalis. Moscow, 233 pp." year="1841">Karelin and Kiriloff (1841)</bibRefCitation>
distributed as Herb. Fischer no. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="83">504</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
